# Markdown Basic Syntax
@divider

Here's the [basic syntax of Markdown](https://www.markdownguide.org/basic-syntax/), which you can use in your `.mq` files for content formatting. Marque supports standard Markdown syntax, as well as some extensions for enhanced functionality.

@callout .info
This keeps the same syntax coverage as the old page, but groups the smaller examples more tightly.
@end callout

## Headings and paragraphs
@divider

@row
@card
### Headings
# Heading level 1
## Heading level 2
### Heading level 3
#### Heading level 4
##### Heading level 5
###### Heading level 6
@end card

@card
### Heading syntax
```md
# Heading level 1
## Heading level 2
### Heading level 3
#### Heading level 4
##### Heading level 5
###### Heading level 6
```
@end card
@end row

@row
@card
### Alternate headings
Heading level 1
===============

Heading level 2
---------------
@end card

@card
### Alternate heading syntax
```md
Heading level 1
===============

Heading level 2
---------------
```
@end card
@end row

@row
@card
### Paragraphs
This is a paragraph.

This is another paragraph.
@end card

@card
### Paragraph and line break syntax
```md
This is a paragraph.

This is another paragraph.

First line.  
Second line.
```
@end card

@card
### Line breaks
First line.  
Second line.
@end card
@end row

## Emphasis and inline syntax
@divider

@row
@card .primary
### Bold, italic, and both
- `**bold text**` or `__bold text__` -> **bold text**
- `*italic text*` or `_italic text_` -> *italic text*
- `***bold and italic***` -> ***bold and italic***
@end card

@card .secondary
### Inline code and escaping
- ``Use `code` like this.`` -> Use `code` like this.
- `\* Not italic \*` -> \* Not italic \*
@end card
@end row

## Blockquotes and lists
@divider

@row
@card
### Blockquotes
Single-line blockquote syntax can stay inline: ``> This is a blockquote.``

> This is a blockquote.

Nested blockquote syntax:
```md
> First level
>
> > Second level
```

> First level
>
> > Second level
@end card

@card
### Lists
Ordered list syntax:
```md
1. First item
2. Second item
3. Third item
```

1. First item
2. Second item
3. Third item

Unordered list syntax:
```md
- First item
- Second item
- Third item
```

- First item
- Second item
- Third item

Nested list syntax:
```md
- Item
  - Subitem
```

- Item
  - Subitem
@end card
@end row

## Code, links, media, and rules
@divider

@row
@card
### Code
Inline code: ``Use `code` like this.``

Use `code` like this.

Code block syntax:
````md
```text
code block
```
````

```text
code block
```
@end card

@card
### Links and images
Link syntax:
`[Google](https://www.google.com)` -> [Google](https://www.google.com)

Image syntax:
```md
![Alt text](https://placehold.co/600x400)
```

![Alt text](https://placehold.co/600x400)
@end card

@card
### Horizontal rules
Any of these will render a horizontal rule:
- `---`
- `***`
- `___`

---
@end card
@end row

## Best Practices
@divider

@card
* Leave blank lines between elements
* Don't indent paragraphs
* Use consistent list markers
* Prefer `*` for emphasis compatibility
@end card
